Burger King in Salford is a fast food restaurant renowned for its flame-grilled beef and crispy chicken options. The menu features popular meals such as the Chicken Royale Meal, Double Whopper Meal, Bacon Double XL Meal, and the Whopper Meal, all frequently enjoyed by customers. For those looking for variety, the restaurant also offers a range of sides like fries and onion rings, alongside a selection of ice creams including Ben & Jerry's Cookie Dough and Chocolate Fudge Brownie. Vegan and plant-based options such as the Plant-Based Whopper Meal and Vegan Royale Meal cater to diverse dietary preferences. The Smokey BBQ Dip is a common choice to complement the Chicken Royale Meal. Less

      • Is breakfast available at Burger King?

        Yes, breakfast is available at Burger King locations across the UK. The breakfast menu typically includes items like the Fully Loaded Croissanwich with Egg, Chicken Strips Croissanwich with Egg, and more.

      • What time does Burger King stop serving breakfast?

        Burger King generally stops serving breakfast at 11:00 AM in the UK. However, its advisable to check the details on this page for Burger King (Salford) as times may vary by location.

      • Is Burger King halal?

        Burger King in the UK does not offer halal-certified food. Its recommended to check with individual locations for specific dietary requirements.

      • Does Burger King serve gluten-free food?

        Burger King in the UK has limited gluten-free options. While they offer items like the Bean Burgers and Vegan Nuggets, these contain gluten. Its best to consult their allergen menu for detailed information.

      • Does Burger King serve vegetarian items?

        Yes, Burger King offers vegetarian items in the UK, including the popular Veggie Bean Burger and other plant-based options.

      • Does Burger King serve vegan items?

        Yes, Burger King serves vegan items in the UK. The menu includes options like the Vegan Royale and Vegan Nuggets, catering to those following a plant-based diet.

      • What are the ingredients in Burger Kings Whopper?

        The Burger King Whopper in the UK typically includes a flame-grilled beef patty, sesame seed bun, mayonnaise, lettuce, tomato, pickles, ketchup, and sliced onions. It is seasoned with salt and pepper to enhance the flavour.

      • What desserts are available on the Burger King menu in the UK?

        Burger King in the UK offers a variety of desserts, including options like the Hersheys Sundae Pie, vanilla soft serve cones, and chocolate sundaes. They may also offer seasonal desserts and limited-time offerings, so its always a good idea to check the current menu at Burger King (Salford).

      • What types of milkshakes does Burger King offer?

        Burger King offers a selection of milkshakes, including popular flavours like chocolate, vanilla, and strawberry. They also have special shakes such as the Oreo Shake, which is a thick and creamy shake blended with Oreo chunks.

      • What is included in Burger Kings Chicken Royale?

        The Chicken Royale at Burger King consists of a long sesame seed bun filled with a crispy chicken fillet, topped with fresh lettuce and creamy mayonnaise. Its a classic choice for chicken sandwich lovers.

      • What are the options for sides at Burger King in the UK?

        Burger King offers a variety of sides, including classic French fries, onion rings, and chicken nuggets. They also have options like chilli cheese bites, halloumi fries, and loaded king fries, which come with different toppings such as bacon or cheese.
